<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What Claude prompts actually work for cold outreach?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The most effective cold outreach prompts give Claude three things: a researched account brief, a specific buyer profile, and a constraint on length (90 words or fewer). Prompts that say 'write me a cold email' produce generic output. Prompts that include the prospect's recent trigger events and a banned-phrases list produce emails that get replies."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I use Claude prompts for sales without a paid plan?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The prompts on this page work on any Claude plan, including the free tier. However, Claude Projects (which let you store a persistent system prompt with your ICP, voice guidelines, and past wins) require Claude Pro or higher. For a team, Claude Team is the minimum recommended plan."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I save a Claude sales prompt so I do not have to re-enter it every time?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Create a Claude Project and paste your system prompt into the Project Instructions field. Every conversation inside that Project inherits the context automatically. You can also upload supporting documents (competitor battlecards, case studies, product one-pagers) as Project knowledge so Claude can reference them without you pasting them each time."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the best Claude prompt for researching a prospect before a sales call?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Prompt 07 on this page (Discovery Call Prep Brief) is designed specifically for pre-call research. Give it the account brief, a LinkedIn summary of the person, and the email thread that led to the meeting. It returns five tailored discovery questions, three relevant proof points, two likely objections, and a list of things you should not say."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I get Claude to write personalized outreach emails instead of generic ones?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Specificity is the lever. Include the prospect's name, company, role, one recent signal (funding, hire, product launch), and a banned-phrases list (no 'circling back', no 'hope this finds you well'). Then ask for three variants with different angles and explain what is different about each. Generic output almost always traces back to a generic prompt."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which Claude model is best for B2B sales prompts?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Claude Sonnet is the best balance of speed and quality for sales use cases like account research, email drafting, and call prep. Claude Opus is worth using for complex, multi-step tasks like proposal drafts or deal diagnosis when you have more time. For high-volume, repetitive tasks like short reply triage, Claude Haiku is fast and cost-effective."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is using Claude for sales different from using ChatGPT?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The main practical difference for sales teams is Claude Projects versus GPT's Custom Instructions. Claude Projects let you store longer system prompts (up to 200K tokens of context) and upload multiple supporting documents per project, which means your ICP, positioning, and past wins persist without re-pasting. Claude also tends to follow explicit constraint lists (like banned phrases) more reliably, which matters a lot for outreach quality."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Claude help diagnose why a sales deal has gone quiet?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Prompt 09 on this page (Stalled Deal Diagnosis) is built for exactly that. Paste in the deal history and email thread, and Claude returns three ranked hypotheses for what is happening on the buyer's side, the most common stall patterns at that deal stage, and a single re-engagement email designed to either unlock the deal or confirm it is dead."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I use Claude to prep for a discovery call?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Use Prompt 07 from this page. Thirty minutes before the call, paste in your account brief, a quick LinkedIn summary of the person you are meeting, and the email thread. Claude returns five open-ended discovery questions tailored to their context, three proof points matched to their situation, two likely objections with suggested responses, and the strongest single reason to take a next step."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a Claude Project and why does it matter for sales teams?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A Claude Project is a persistent workspace inside Claude where you store a system prompt and supporting documents. For sales teams, it means every conversation with Claude already knows your ICP, your product positioning, your banned phrases, and your top customer wins. You do not have to re-explain your company every time. It makes every prompt on this page significantly more accurate and on-voice."}}]}</script>
