    <p class="body">These prompts are 10x more powerful inside a properly configured Claude Project than copy-pasted into a fresh chat each time. The Project gives Claude persistent context: your ICP, your voice, your company's positioning, your past sales wins.</p>
    <p class="body">For the full setup walkthrough, see our <a href="/resources/how-to-build-a-claude-project-for-your-team" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">guide to building a Claude Project for your team</a>. Or if you want this built for you across all of GTM, our <a href="/services/implementation" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Implementation engagement</a> includes building Sales, Marketing, and RevOps Claude Projects with your specific configurations.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Frequently asked questions</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Questions about using Claude prompts for sales</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What Claude prompts actually work for cold outreach?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">The most effective cold outreach prompts give Claude three inputs: a researched account brief, a specific buyer profile, and a hard constraint on length (90 words or fewer). Prompts that simply say "write me a cold email" produce generic output. Prompts that include the prospect's recent trigger events and a banned-phrases list produce emails that get replies. See Prompt 04 above for the full structure.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can I use Claude prompts for sales without a paid plan?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">The prompts on this page work on any Claude plan, including the free tier. However, Claude Projects (which let you store a persistent system prompt with your ICP, voice guidelines, and past wins) require Claude Pro or higher. For a team sharing prompts and context, Claude Team is the minimum recommended plan.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do I save a sales prompt so I do not have to re-enter it every time?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Create a Claude Project and paste your system prompt into the Project Instructions field. Every conversation inside that Project inherits the context automatically. You can also upload supporting documents (battlecards, case studies, product one-pagers) as Project knowledge so Claude can reference them without you pasting them each time.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is the best Claude prompt for researching a prospect before a sales call?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Prompt 07 on this page (Discovery Call Prep Brief) is designed for exactly this. Give it the account brief, a LinkedIn summary of the person, and the email thread that led to the meeting. It returns five tailored discovery questions, three relevant proof points, two likely objections, and a list of things you should not say in the call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How is using Claude for sales different from using ChatGPT?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">The main practical difference for sales teams is Claude Projects versus GPT's Custom Instructions. Claude Projects support longer system prompts and let you upload multiple supporting documents per project, so your ICP, positioning, and past wins persist without re-pasting. Claude also tends to follow explicit constraint lists (like banned phrases) more reliably in practice, which matters a lot for outreach quality.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Which Claude model is best for B2B sales prompts?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Claude Sonnet is the best balance of speed and quality for most sales use cases: account research, email drafting, and call prep. Claude Opus is worth using for complex, multi-step tasks like proposal drafts or deal diagnosis when you have more time. For high-volume, repetitive tasks like short reply triage, Claude Haiku is fast and cost-effective.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can Claude help diagnose why a sales deal has gone quiet?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Prompt 09 (Stalled Deal Diagnosis) is built for this. Paste in the deal history and email thread, and Claude returns three ranked hypotheses for what is happening on the buyer's side, the most common stall patterns at that stage, and a single re-engagement email designed to either unlock the deal or confirm it is dead.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

